Kevin Bollaert, 28, was convicted in February of 21 counts of identity theft and six counts of extortion in San Diego Superior Court .
He ran a 'revenge porn' site that capitalized on the internet as a forum for public shaming .
More than 10,000 images, mainly of women, were posted between December 2012 and September 2013 .
Bollaert earned about $900 a month in ad revenue and collected about $30,000 from victims .